{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> καρπόω</b>, <br /> <b>bear fruit</b> or <b>bear as fruit</b>, <i>metaphorically</i>, ὕβρις γὰρ ἐξανθοῦσ᾽ ἐκάρπωσε στάχυν ἄτης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 821 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, τὰ πλεῖστα τῶν ῥιζοφύτων καρπωθέντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC(?): Ocellus Lucanus Philosophus 1.13. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>offer</b> by way of sacrifice, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Lev.2.11 \">LXX</a>]; ἐπὶ τοῦ βωμοῦ, of burnt-offerings, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1025.33 (Cos, 4th-3rd c.BC):\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —so in <i>passive</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\", [prev. work]997.9 (from Smyrna),compare 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>take as fruit</b> or <b>produce</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Deu.26.14:—elsewhere in \">LXX</a>]<i>middle</i>, καρπόομαι <b>get fruit for oneself</b>, i.e., <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> <b>reap crops from</b>, with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, [ἀρούρας] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.168; Χθόνα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 851, “Supp.” 253 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δὶς τοῦ ἐνιαυτοῦ τὴν γῆν καρποῦσθαι <b>to crop</b> the land twice a year, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 118e: _metaphorically_, βαθεῖαν ἄλοκα διὰ φρενὸς καρπούμενος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 593 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: hence, <b>exhaust, drain, exploit</b>, καρπουμένῳ τὴν Ἑλλάδα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 520, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.133,166; οὐσίας 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.249. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>enjoy the usufruct</b> or <b>interest</b> of money, ἔδωκεν ἑβδομήκοντα μνᾶς καρπώσασθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 27.5 \">Refs</a>]; τοὺς λιμένας καὶ τὰς ἀγορὰς καρποῦσθαι <b>to derive profits from.. </b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.22; ἔθνη 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 6.1.12; ἰδία κ. τὰς τῆς πόλεως συμφοράς 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 25.25 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [πλεονεξίαν] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 23.126: in \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i>, τὸ ἐργαστήριον κεκαρπωμένος <b>having enjoyed the profits</b> of the shop, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 27.47 \">Refs</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>make profit</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 837. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>enjoy the free use of</b>, τὰ αὐτοῦ ἀγαθὰ γιγνόμενα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.38 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὴν τῶν πολεμίων [Χώραν], τὰς τῶν θεῶν τιμάς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Agesilaus” 1.34 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὴν οἰκείαν ἀδεῶς κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 1.25, compare 28. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> simply, <b>enjoy</b>, ἄελπτον ὄμμα.. φήμης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 204; τἀμὰ.. λέχη 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 935; ἐλευθερίαν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.68; τὴν σοφίαν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 305e; ἡδονὴν ταύτην [prev. author] “Phdr.” 252a, compare 240a, etc.; ἀσφάλειαν καὶ εὔκλειαν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.2.22; τὴν δόξαν τινός 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.69; τὴν ἡλικίαν [prev. author] 59.19; δωρεάς 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Themistocles” 31 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in bad sense, ἰδίας καρποῦσθαι λύπας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ φυσῶν” 1; φρενῶν τὴν ἁμαρτίαν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 502 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ ψευδῆ καλά[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 621; πένθη 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 1427; ἄπαιδα κ. βίον [prev. author] “fragment” 571.3; τὰ μέγιστα ὀνείδη 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 183a; λοιδορίας 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ κακιῶν ί” p.34J. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7805","accentedUnicode":"καρπόω","shortDef":"to yield","mediumDef":"to yield","stepGloss":"to yield","stepTransliteration":"karpoō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}